        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 9:12AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 912 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Heiberger to 8 miles northeast of Marion
Junction to near Orrville to near Camden. Movement was east at 50
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hayneville, Stanton, Carlowville, Robert F. Henry Lock And Dam,
Parnell, Tyler, Autauga County Airport, Selma, Craig Field Aiport,
Plantersville, Dannelly Reservoir, Verbena, Selmont-West Selmont,
Mulberry, Marbury, Valley Grande, Whites Bluff, Paul M Grist State
Park, Letohatchee, and Mitchell Dam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for
central, south central and east central Alabama.</instruction>
